text = "What Rituals Can Pay For"

[node name="CostText" type="RichTextLabel" parent="Margin/VBox/Scroll/ContentRoot/PayCard/Inner"]
layout_mode = 2
bbcode_enabled = false
fit_content = true
scroll_active = false
text = "Rituals are the engine of the game — every other card type is paid for with your Rituals, either by having the matching active lane or by sacrificing Rituals.

- Incantations — active lane of matching value, or sacrifice Rituals totaling at least the cost.
- Lower Nobles (cost 4 or less) — active lane only. Sacrifice cannot pay for them.
- Higher Nobles (cost 6 or more) — sacrifice only. Active lanes cannot pay for them.
- Temples — sacrifice only. Most Temples cost 7; Ytria, Temple of Cycles, costs 9.
- Rings — all Rings cost 2, so an active 2-lane (or higher active lane) is required. Sacrifice cannot pay for Rings.
- Birds — active lane of matching cost. Sacrifice cannot pay for Birds.

Example (cards below): with active 1-, 2-, and 3-Rituals you can play anything whose cost lane is active — an Incantation (Woe 3), a Lower Noble (Trss, cost 3), a Ring (Sybiline, cost 2), and a Bird (Sparrow, cost 2). See the Temple Payment and Higher vs Lower Nobles sections below for sacrifice-based plays."

